buy(uint256[],uint256[],(bytes32[],bool[.details: DO NOT call this function directly unless you know what you are doing. Instead, use a wrapper contract that will check the max input amount and revert if the slippage is too high.

params.proof: The merkle proof for the weights of each NFT to buy.
params.tokenIds: The token IDs of the NFTs to buy.
params.tokenWeights: The weights of the NFTs to buy.

returns.feeAmount: The amount of base tokens spent on fees.
returns.netInputAmount: The amount of base tokens spent inclusive of fees.

params.outputAmount: The amount of NFTs to buy multiplied by 1e18.

returns.netInputAmount: The required input amount of base tokens inclusive of the fee.

params.inputTokenIds: The token IDs of the NFTs to change.

params.inputAmount: The amount of NFTs to change multiplied by 1e18.

constructor.details: This is only called when the base implementation contract is deployed. The following immutable parameters are set: - factory: The address of the factory contract - royaltyRegistry: The address of the royalty registry from manifold.xyz - stolenNftOracle: The address of the stolen NFT oracle These are all stored in immutable storage, which enables all minimal proxy contracts to read them without incurring additional deployment costs and re-initializing them at point of creation in the factory contract.

params.data: The data to send to the target contract.
params.target: The address of the target contract.

returns._0: returnData The return data of the transaction.

params._baseToken: The address of the base token
params._useStolenNftOracle: Whether or not the pool uses the stolen NFT oracle to check if an NFT is stolen

returns._0: price The price of the pool.

sell(uint256[],uint256[],(bytes32[],bool.details: DO NOT call this function directly unless you know what you are doing. Instead, use a wrapper contract that will check the min output amount and revert if the slippage is too high.

params.proof: The merkle proof for the weights of each NFT to sell.
params.stolenNftProofs: The proofs that show each NFT is not stolen.
params.tokenIds: The token IDs of the NFTs to sell.
params.tokenWeights: The weights of the NFTs to sell.

returns.feeAmount: The amount of base tokens to pay in fees.
returns.netOutputAmount: The amount of base tokens received inclusive of fees.

params.inputAmount: The amount of NFTs to sell multiplied by 1e18.

returns.netOutputAmount: The output amount of base tokens inclusive of the fee.

params.proof: The merkle proof for the weights of each NFT.
params.tokenIds: The token IDs of the NFTs to sum the weights for.
params.tokenWeights: The weights of each NFT in the token IDs array.

returns._0: sum The sum of the weights of each NFT.

baseToken().notice: The address of the base ERC20 token.

buy(uint256[],uint256[],(bytes32[],bool[.notice: Buys NFTs from the pool, paying with base tokens from the caller. Then transfers the bought NFTs to the caller. The net cost depends on the current price, fee rate and assigned NFT weights.

buyQuote(uint256).notice: Returns the required input of buying a given amount of NFTs inclusive of the fee which is dependent on the currently set fee rate.

change(uint256[],uint256[]).notice: Changes a set of NFTs that the caller owns for another set of NFTs in the pool. The caller must approve the pool to transfer the NFTs. The sum of the caller's NFT weights must be less than or equal to the sum of the output pool NFTs weights. The caller must also pay a fee depending the net input weight and change fee amount.

changeFee().notice: The change/flash fee to 4 decimals of precision. For example, 0.0025 ETH = 25. 500 USDC = 5_000_000.

changeFeeQuote(uint256).notice: Returns the fee required to change a given amount of NFTs. The fee is based on the current changeFee (which contains 4 decimals of precision) multiplied by some exponent depending on the base token decimals.

execute(address,bytes).notice: Executes a transaction from the pool account to a target contract. The caller must be the owner of the pool. This allows for use cases such as claiming airdrops.

factory().notice: The factory contract that created this pool.

feeRate().notice: The buy/sell fee rate (in basis points) 200 = 2%

initialize(address,address,uint128,uint1.notice: Initializes the private pool and sets the initial parameters. Should only be called once by the factory.

initialized().notice: Whether or not the pool has been initialized.

merkleRoot().notice: The merkle root of all the token weights in the pool. If the merkle root is set to bytes32(0) then all NFTs are set to have a weight of 1e18.

payRoyalties().notice: Whether or not the pool pays royalties to the NFT creator on each trade.

price().notice: Returns the price of the pool to 18 decimals of accuracy.

sell(uint256[],uint256[],(bytes32[],bool.notice: Sells NFTs into the pool and transfers base tokens to the caller. NFTs are transferred from the caller to the pool. The net sale amount depends on the current price, fee rate and assigned NFT weights.

sellQuote(uint256).notice: Returns the output amount of selling a given amount of NFTs inclusive of the fee which is dependent on the currently set fee rate.

stolenNftOracle().notice: The NFT oracle to check if an NFT is stolen.

sumWeightsAndValidateProof(uint256[],uin.notice: Sums the weights of each NFT and validates that the weights are correct by verifying the merkle proof.

useStolenNftOracle().notice: Whether or not the pool uses the stolen NFT oracle to check if an NFT is stolen.

virtualBaseTokenReserves().notice: The virtual base token reserves used in the xy=k invariant. Changing this will change the liquidity depth and price of the pool.

virtualNftReserves().notice: The virtual nft reserves used in the xy=k invariant. Changing this will change the liquidity depth and price of the pool.
